    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1911-01-16T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1911-01-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="738"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d738">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 815.51/169 a.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Minister</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1911-01-16">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 16, 1911</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The text of the loan convention sent you January 3 is entirely accurate except
                    last paragraph should read “Done in duplicate at Washington this tenth day of
                    January one thousand nine hundred and eleven” and [the same in Spanish]; and is
                    signed “Philander C. Knox, Juan E. Paredes.”</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Knox.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
